===Proverb===
{{head|en|proverb}}

# {{non-gloss definition|An expression of [[willingness]], even [[eagerness]], to give one's life for a [[cause#Noun|cause]].}}
#* {{quote-book|author=Stephen Solomita|chapter=12|title=A Good Day to Die|location=New York, N.Y.|publisher=[[w:Otto Penzler|Otto Penzler Books]]|year=1993|isbn=978-1-883402-03-7|passage=Junkies brag about the "rush" of mainlined heroin or inhaled crack cocaine; I'll put the rush of danger up against any drug. I wasn't kidding when I told Bouton it was '''a good day to die'''. ''Any'' day is '''a good day to die'''. As long as you go down fighting.|brackets=on}}
#* {{quote-book|author=Robert B[rown] Parker|authorlink=Robert B. Parker|chapter=26|title=[[w:Night Passage (novel)|Night Passage: A Jesse Stone Novel]]|location=New York, N.Y.|publisher={{w|G. P. Putnam's Sons}}|year=1997|isbn=978-0-399-14304-5|passage=We will keep safe the heritage of this country. And if someday we must die to serve this cause, well, then, it will be '''a good day to die'''.|brackets=on}}
#* {{quote-journal|magazine=[[w:Engineering News-Record|Engineering News-Record: Top Construction Management Firms]]|location=New York, N.Y.|publisher=[[w:McGraw-Hill Education|McGraw-Hill]]|year=2001|volume 246|page=72|issn=0891-9526|oclc=20849177|passage=Otherwise, small business owners like those in the construction industry will have to be prescient, as well as politically and financially astute, in deciding if '''today is a good day to die'''.}}
# {{non-gloss definition|An expression indicating that one should not live with any [[regret#Noun|regrets]], or [[task#Noun|tasks]] left undone.}}
#* {{quote-book|author=Dave Collins|chapter=Gains|title=Please Remain Seated until the Ride has Come to a Complete Stop: Dave Collins Memoir|location=Lincoln, Neb.|publisher=Writer's Showcase, {{w|iUniverse}}|year=2002|pages=86–87|pageurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=aTDnhjYu77gC&pg=PA87|isbn=978-0-595-21342-9|passage=To be given the strength to live without regrets, without the feeling that you should be doing something more, something different. To make ''today'' '''a good day to die'''. To gain fulfillment not with length of time, but with quality.}}
#* {{quote-book|author=Dan Millman|authorlink=Dan Millman|chapter=On Chapter Four: The Sword is Sharpened|title=Wisdom of the Peaceful Warrior: A Companion to the Book that Changes Lives|location=Tilburon, Calif.|publisher=H. J. Kramer; Novato, Calif.: {{w|New World Library}}|year=2006|page=111|pageurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=wY601VuaYoQC&pg=PA111|isbn=978-1-932073-21-8|passage=The main thing is to die after having truly lived, after leaving behind a contribution. {{w|Socrates}} lived fully and was perfectly content to let go when the time came. As the Native American saying goes, "'''Today is a good day to die'''."}}
#* {{quote-book|author=John Izzo|authorlink=John Izzo|chapter=The First Secret: Be True to Your Self|title=The Five Secrets You must Discover before You Die|location=San Francisco, Calif.|publisher={{w|Berrett-Koehler Publishers}}|year=2008|page=43|pageurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=orE-u3FZphkC&pg=PA43|isbn=978-1-57675-475-7|passage=In the native tradition of the Pacific Northwest there is a saying: "'''Today is a good day to die'''." What it means, of course, is that today is a good day to live completely. If you were lying on that hospital bed right now, what would be on that short list?}}

